    "plan_content": "## Plan: `Bun.INI` namespace — parse + stringify\n\nI explored the full codebase and have a precise, step-by-step plan. Here's what needs to happen:\n\n---\n\n### Why a new parser? The existing `src/ini.zig`\nThere's already an INI parser at `src/ini.zig`, but it's coupled to the package manager — it requires a `DotEnv.Loader` argument for `${VAR}` environment variable expansion. It can't be used for a clean public API. A new self-contained parser goes in `src/interchange/ini.zig`.\n\n---\n\n### 7 files total (2 new, 5 modified)\n\n**New files:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/interchange/ini.zig` | Self-contained parser → `Expr` AST. Handles `[sections]`, `key=value`, `;`/`#` comments, value coercion (true/false/null/numbers), CRLF |\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | JS API: `parse()` (mirrors JSONCObject) + `stringify()` (inline Stringifier producing flat `key=value` then `[section]` blocks) |\n| `test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts` | Tests for parse, stringify, round-trips, edge cases |\n\n**Modified files (small targeted additions):**\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/interchange.zig` | +1 line: `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | +1 line: `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | +4 insertions at 4 known line numbers: property decl, export, getter fn, import alias |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | +1 line: `macro(INI) \\` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER` |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | +1 line in lookup table: `INI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback` |",
